#8301
Kevin's Watch~


The mountains rising dramatically here seem to strike you a 
blow. They spring upwards out of the clouds a stone's throw
from the Watch. Their peaks are rugged and dour. From the 
cliff behind the Watch, the mountains withdraw on both sides
like a wedge, piling higher into the distance.  Off to the
distant northeast, like a giant granite spur, stands Mount
Thunder.


