#8337
Before the Great Keep of Revelstone~


You stand before the great stone city, Revelstone. Giant-wrought
millenia ago from the gutrock of the plateau, it towers before 
you, untouched by time.  Out of the farthest west, mountains came 
striding eastward, then, two leagues away on your left, drop sheer 
to the upland plateau, still a thousand feet more above the 
foothills. The plateau narrowed to form a wedged promontory
half a league in length and into this promontory the ancient 
Giants have delved the immense and intricate habitation of 
Revelstone. 


