#8383
Before Lord Foul's Creche~


The promontory rises to a high pile of rock at its tip, and there stands
Lord Foul's Creche. Two matched towers, as tall and slender as minarets,
rising several hundred feet into the air, and between them at ground level
is the dark open hole of a single entrance. The dark windows of the twin
towers gape blindly back at you like soulless eyes, hollow and abhorred.
The mouth of Foul's Creche is smooth and symmetrical, unadorned, perfectly
made. The opening stands in a massive abutment of wrought stone---a polished
fortification which cups the entrance as if it leads to a sacred crypt.


