#8384
Main Hall of the Creche~


You find yourselves in the narrow end of an egg shaped hall. Its stonework
and symmetry are perfect. At its widest point, it opens into matched passages
which appear to lead up into the towers, and the floor of the opposite end
sinks flawlessly down to form a wide, spiral stairway into the rock. The
unblemished features of the hall suggest the ideal conception of its creator
have been rendered into immaculate stone without the interference of hands
that slip, minds that misunderstood.


